CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 26, 1952, page 2, reads: "NAACP Youth Elect - The NAACP Youth Council recently had its election and installation of officers for 1952. Shown above are the new officers and some of them members. They are, left to right (seated), Dorothy Kendricks, corresponding secretary; Adeline Blackman, treasurer; Gloria Fuller; president; Melusena Carl, vice president, and Roselee Moore, recording secretary. Standing: Julius Mixon, sports chairman; Doris Thomas, social chairman; Fannie Campbell, program chairman; Delores Thomas and Edmon Davis, sports co-chairman. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: NAACP Youth Council seated from left: corresponding secretary Dorothy Kendrick, treasurer Adeline Blackman, president Gloria Fuller, vice president Melusena Carl, recording secretary Roselee Moore; standing: sports chairman Julius Mixon, social chairman Doris Thomas, program chairman Fannie Campbell, Delores Thomas, and sports co-chairman Edmon Davis, in interior with square patterned curtains
